The paper deals with a problem of searching and fetching in a distributed environment using robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The problem involves designing distributed algorithms, which can be categorized under distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The use of wireless and face-to-face communication protocols also suggests a focus on networking and communication, which can be categorized under multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and systems and control (cs.SY).
